{
  "texts": [
    "This ratio was chosen to provide sufficient data for training while also allowing adequate samples for validation and testing.",
    "Given the complexity of the model, the 80/10/10 split ensures that more data is available for training.",
    "Furthermore, given the large size of the dataset, 10% of the data points used for validation and testing are sufficient to validate and test effectively.",
    "We used the Kolmogorov-Smirnov test 6, a nonparametric test of the equality of continuous probability distributions, to verify that there were no significant differences (train vs validation: p =.36, train vs test:.91, validation vs test: p =.75) between the label distributions in the train, validation and test sets 7.",
    "Learning rate, batch size, and weight decay were selected on the validation set using grid search from {1e-6, 1e-5, 2e-5, 3e-5, 5e-5, 1e-4}, {32, 64, 128, 256, 512} and {0.01, 0.02, 0.03, 0.05, 0.08, 0.1} respectively."
  ]
}